    //       "PenLink is a technology company bringing clarity to complex data for people who need it now. We partner with law enforcement agencies across the United States, Canada, and Europe, offering a highly-available, cloud-native software solution to manage data and aid investigators solving crimes. PenLink uses artificial intelligence, big data, and visualization technologies to support analysts who are improving the world and keeping safe the place we call home. \n<br>\n<br> We are dedicated to creating products that make a positive impact on our communities and embody our core mission. Driven by our “get it done” attitude, we are experiencing unprecedented growth and are now looking for a talented Software Engineer to join our dynamic Product Development Division. This position plays an integral role in ensuring that we deliver the highest quality product to our clients. \n<br>\n<br> The Software Engineer will be responsible for the delivery of new features, building and maintaining cloud infrastructure, monitoring/operations, and bug fixes within our web-based analysis tools while working closely with the Product Development, DevOps, Quality Assurance and Design teams. PenLink's Canadian team is based in downtown Toronto and team members enjoy a hybrid work environment. \n<br>\n<br>   \n<br>\n<br> YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Producing high quality, well tested, scalable code \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Delivering features and software fixes on-time and to specification \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Completing unit and integration tests with measured code coverage for features and bugs \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Understanding our software architecture, adhering to corporate design principles and standards, and following best practices and processes \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Supporting the integrity of the conceptual design of the assigned subsystem \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Taking work as needed to make sure that all team members complete sprint items within the sprint duration \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Notifying the Team Lead or other leaders of any subsystem risks that could impact usability, release dates, or client issues \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Coordinating with teams across the organization to gain a complete understanding of all issues and requirements \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Authoring white papers for clarification of requirements to aid in designing and pre-planning efforts \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Identifying, designing, and executing subsystem stress tests and resulting performance limits \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Completing code reviews for work completed by peers \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Actively participating in our “Air Traffic Controller” rotation, responding to alerts and issues impacting our live systems during business hours \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Other responsibilities as assigned \n<br>\n<br> YOUR COMPETENCIES \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>At least 2 years of experience building web-based applications with JavaScript. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>At least 2 years of experience writing software using either Java or C#; experience with Spring Boot a plus. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Experience with modern Single-Page-Application frameworks such as React or VueJS. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Familiarity working with cloud technologies such as Amazon Web Services or Microsoft Azure. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Knowledge of relational database technologies, preferably MySQL. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Experience developing and integration with REST APIs. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Knowledge of Docker and Docker Swarm is highly desirable \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Working knowledge of Elasticsearch is highly desirable. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Knowledge of Python and Go are beneficial. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Experience building user interfaces, data visualization, and software people love to use \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Desire to learn new technologies as the project requirements evolve. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>A team player who communicates well and improves project quality by both providing and accepting critical feedback in a professional manner. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Detail-oriented, methodical, and organized. \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>\n<br> YOUR EDUCATION &amp; EXPERIENCE \n<br>\n<br> • \n<br>Bachelor's degree in Engineering, Computer Science, related 4-year technical degree or equivalent real-world experience",
