    //       '<div>\n <p><b>Location: Richmond Hill, ON (Hybrid) </b></p>\n <p>This is a hybrid position primarily based in Richmond Hill, ON. We’re committed to your flexibility and wellbeing and our hybrid strategy currently requires three days a week in the office, giving you the option to work remotely for some of your working week. Find out more about our culture of flexible working. </p>\n <p><b>We give you a world of potential </b></p>\n <p>Computershare has an exciting opportunity available for a permanent full-time Senior Software Developer to join our talented and collaborative Computershare Communication Services (CCS) team in our Richmond Hill, ON office.<br> </p>\n <p><br> <b>A role you will love </b></p>\n <p>In this role, you’ll be responsible for delivering high quality client communications applications and report to the Software Development Team Lead. You will be partaking in the development and delivery of high quality, robust programs in adherence to established standards and procedures. As this is a senior position, we are seeking an individual with solid time management, organization, leadership, and mentoring skills. A keen eye for detail, strong time-management, problem solving, communication and prioritization skills are integral to this position. </p>\n <p><b>Key responsibilities include: </b></p>\n <ul>\n  <li>Designing and coding quality programs that work with various data sources using Perl, Quadient Inspire and interacting with SQL Server </li>\n  <li>Completing all deliverables on schedule and within estimated time limits </li>\n  <li>Learning and providing support for all internal systems from troubleshooting, maintenance, and system upgrades to provide high availability of business systems </li>\n  <li>Adherence to departmental and company standards, processes, and procedures. </li>\n  <li>Performing review on the solution design, architecture, and code of peer developers to maintain quality and standards </li>\n  <li>Facilitating training and knowledge transfer between team members to enhance deliver of overall objectives </li>\n  <li>Identifying and supporting business innovation initiatives such as process improvement, on-boarding new technologies, improvements to existing technologies, minimizing technical debt to ensure optimal operational efficiency </li>Liaising with Business Analysts, Quality Analysts, Project Managers, and other areas of the business to deliver client and business requirements to provide the best customer experience \n </ul>\n <p><br> <b>What will you bring to the role? </b></p>\n <p>You have a curious mindset with a strong desire to learn and stay up to date with the latest technologies. You also have strong problem-solving skills which enable you to identify root cause and provide solutions to critical problems. You’re self-motivated with the ability to work both autonomously and in a team environment.<br> </p>\n <p></p>\n <p><b>You’ll also bring: </b></p>\n <ul>\n  <li>5+ years’ programming experience in a professional environment working with object-oriented languages (e.g., Perl, C#, VB.NET, Java, and Python) and SQL databases (MS SQL, MySQL, Oracle); preference for experience with Perl and MS SQL in a Windows environment </li>\n  <li>Experience working with version control systems such as Git, TFVC, etc. </li>\n  <li>Knowledge of various file formats and data standards (Flat, XML, HTML, JSON, YAML, multi record structures, etc.) </li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of OODP and desire to deliver highly efficient and maintainable applications </li>\n </ul>\n <p><b>Bonus points if you have </b>: </p>\n <ul>\n  <li>Degree in Computer Science or related discipline </li>\n  <li>Experience working CI/CD pipeline tools such as Jenkins, Azure DevOps, Microsoft Team Foundation Server </li>\n  <li>Experience working with reporting tools such as PowerBI and SSRS </li>\n  <li>Experience working with Quadient Inspire </li>Software architectural design and leadership experience \n  <li> <br> </li>\n </ul>\n <p><br> <b>Rewards designed for you </b></p>\n <p><b>Flexible work </b>to help you find the best balance between work and lifestyle. </p>\n <p><b>Health and wellbeing </b>rewards that can be tailored to support you and your family. </p>\n <p><b>Invest in our business </b>by setting aside salary to purchase shares in our company, and you’ll receive a company contribution as well. </p>\n <p><b>Extra rewards </b>ranging from recognition awards and team get togethers to helping you invest in your future. </p>\n <p><b>And more. </b>Ours is a welcoming and close-knit community, with experienced colleagues ready to help you grow. Our handbook will help you find out more about our rewards and life at Computershare, visit computershare.com/careers-handbook . </p>\n <p>#LI-Hybrid #LI-SM1</p>\n</div>',
